attachments.text:
Get ready to spice things up at our MBA Chili Competition! It's time to put your culinary skills to the test and show off your family's secret chili recipe.
Bring your A-game, your appetite, and your competitive spirit. Whether you're a chili connoisseur or a first-time cook, this event is for you. Prizes, bragging rights, and, of course, the coveted title of "MBA Chili Champion" are up for grabs.
Don't miss out on this sizzling opportunity to connect, compete, and enjoy some delicious chili!
Award categories will include: Best Overall, Most like Mom's, Best Smoked Chili, Best Sweet & Spicy Chili, and People's Choice Award.
 
*Please include a serving spoon or ladle and remember to label your items!
**It doesn't matter which group you sign up in, it's just the easiest format on this sign up platform.

<!channel> :bangbang:*REMINDER: LDB FAIR TOMORROW (Wednesday, 10/4) 3:30-4:30 p.m. in TNRB 710!!!* :alert:

"LDB" = Learn, Do, Become. You probably remember hearing about "LDB's" during orientation. The MBA program has quite a few LDB's, so come learn about all of the different ways you can put into practice the skills and concepts you're learning and gain real-world experience through the LDB of your choice.

The timing of this LDB fair is so that you can have a good idea of which LDB you want to pursue and/or join when class bidding and registration rolls around next week.

text:
FIRST YEARS! Reminder: Rothschild & Co investment banking info session is tomorrow. If you are interested in IB even a little, this is your chance to check it out (if you plan to apply for their internship, you should be there). Additionally, if you are interested in IB exit opportunities (i.e., PE or search fund), IB is a valuable place to start and you should go.

Time/place: Wed Oct 4 from 6:00-7:00pm in TNRB 280.

Some benefits you can expect from a role with Rothschild & Co:
• Opportunity to directly shape and determine the course of the world
• Strategic position where you will work directly with the C-suite of multiple companies
• Group of ambitious, supportive and collaborative people
• $175k base salary (pro-rated for internship) + annual bonus of up to $175k (full-time)
• $60k starting bonus + $10k moving stipend
• 5 weeks vacation + banking holidays + unlimited sick days
• Daily free dinners + ubers + other perks
If you plan to attend, register on handshake (link below).

<https://byu.joinhandshake.com/stu/events/1363807?ref=events-search|https://byu.joinhandshake.com/stu/events/1363807?ref=events-search>

I recommend dressing up for the event. For reference, a suit without a tie is how I'll be dressed. Join the IB Slack channel to connect/share tips with others: <#C0433QH7AA3|investment-banking>
